<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - HIGH PRESSURE OIL PUMP -
        Removal
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Removal</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="3">
            <title>High Pressure Oil Pump Reservoir</title>
            <figure id="f1201102" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3277.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing the Oil From the High Pressure Oil Pump Reservoir</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Hand Operated Vacuum Pump</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">High Pressure Oil Pump Reservoir</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pipe plug from top left side of high pressure oil pump reservoir. Use a hand
                    operated vacuum pump to extract the oil from the reservoir.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the power steering pump.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1201118" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3286.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>EBP Sensor Location</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Sensor Bracket Bolts (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Sensor</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Sensor Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EBP Sensor Tube Nuts</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two bolts that secure the EBP sensor bracket to the right side of the high
                    pressure oil pump reservoir.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the EBP sensor tube from the right exhaust manifold.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1201104" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3198.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing the Mounting Bolts From the High Pressure Oil Pump Reservoir</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">High Pressure Oil Pump Reservoir</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the five mounting bolts that secure the high pressure oil pump reservoir to the
                    front cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the high pressure oil pump reservoir and gasket. Clean all RTV sealant (if used)
                    from the mating surfaces of the high pressure oil pump reservoir and crankcase front cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two bolts that secure the high pressure oil pump access cover (located on the
                    crankcase front cover, directly above water pump). Clean all RTV sealant from the access cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
